{{Infobox company | name = Bresser | native_name = Bresser GmbH | native_name_lang = | romanized = | logo = Bresser GmbH logo.png | logo_size = 250px | caption = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | slogan = | type = | traded_as = | foundation = 1957 | founder = | location = [[Rhede]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = | products = [[telescope]], [[microscope]] | services = | market_cap = | homepage = {{URL|bresser.de}} | footnotes = }}
The '''Bresser Corporation''' is a [[Germany]]-based manufacturer of [[binoculars]], [[telescope]]s and [[microscope]]s.
==History== Bresser GmbH was founded by Josef Bresser in 1957.<ref name="profile">http://www.bresser.de/c/en/bresser-gmbh/company-profile/</ref> The company began by specializing in the import and distribution of binoculars.<ref name="Rosenbauer2003">{{cite book|author=Karlheinz A. Rosenbauer|title=Mikroskopische Präparate|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XPwDuHAaqgQC&pg=PA12|date=16 June 2003|publisher=[[John Wiley & Sons]]|isbn=978-3-928865-36-4|pages=12–}}</ref> Rolf Bresser sold his father's business in 1999 to the [[United States|American]] company [[Meade Instruments]] in Irvine, California, the company operating under Meade Instruments Europe GmbH until 2009, when it was acquired by former owner Rolf Bresser, its general manager, Helmut Ebbert, and Chinese manufacturer Jinghua Optical Electronics Co., Ltd. (JOC).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astronomy.com/news/2013/05/meade-instruments-corp-to-be-acquired-by-jinghua-optics--electronics|title=Meade Instruments Corp. to be acquired by Jinghua Optics & Electronics|work=Astronomy.com|accessdate=18 January 2015}}</ref>
In 2005 the Bresser Messier Line of fine telescopes for the intermediate astronomy passionate was launched.<ref>{{cite book|title=Orion|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_twzAQAAIAAJ|year=2008|language=German|page=54}}</ref> In the US the distribution firm Bresser LLC was founded in 2010.
