{{Infobox person | name = Jim Roth | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = Entrepreneur, businessman and author | alma_mater = [[University of Cambridge]] | years_active = | known_for = Co-founder, [[LeapFrog Investments]] | notable_works = }}
'''Jim Roth''' is a businessman, [[Social entrepreneurship|social entrepreneur]] and author.<ref name =bloom>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=131240266&privcapId=60499309&previousCapId=60499309&previousTitle=LeapFrog%20Investments|title=Executive Profile Jim Roth Ph.D.|publisher=Bloomberg}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.milkeninstitute.org/events/conferences/summit/london-2014/speaker-detail/17223|title=Jim Roth|publisher=Milken Institute}}</ref> He is the co-founder of [[LeapFrog Investments]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/prudential-financial-to-invest-350-million-in-african-insurers-1453469558|title=Prudential Financial to Invest $350 Million in African Insurers|publisher=The Wall Street Journal|author=Simon Clark|date=22 January 2016}}</ref> a [[social finance]] and [[Impact investing|impact investment]] firm that manages investments of more than $1 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/09/15/emerging-markets-can-satisfy-demand-for-return-and-ethics-says-private-equity-firm.html|title=Emerging Markets Can Satisfy Demand For Ethical Investing, Says Strategist|publisher=CNBC|author=Luke Graham|date=15 September 2016}}</ref>
==Biography== Roth received a degree in [[Development Economics]] from the [[University of Manchester]] and a PhD from the [[University of Cambridge]].<ref name=bloom/> While working towards his PhD, Roth spent time examining how individuals with a low income used financial services.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/413d68dc-2c22-11e7-9ec8-168383da43b7|title=LeapFrog Targets Private Equity Gains in Africa and Asia|publisher=Financial Times|first=Attracta|last=Mooney|date=May 12, 2017}}</ref>
Prior to co-founding Leapfrog, he worked for the United Nations agency, [[International Labour Organization]] (ILO), in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://empea.org/about/leadership-governance/jim-roth|title=Jim Roth|publisher=EMPEA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/e3714822-c10f-11e1-8179-00144feabdc0|title=Investor Reaches Out to Underserved Sector|publisher=Financial Times|author=Sophia Grene|date=1 July 2012}}</ref> During his time at the ILO, Roth co-authored the book, ''Making Insurance Work for Microfinance Institutions''. Roth has appeared on ''[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]]'' and ''[[CNBC]]'' discussing issues around the rise of the emerging consumer demographic and the role of financial services in emerging markets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2015-09-03/where-are-the-opportunities-in-emerging-markets-|title=Where Are the Opportunities in emerging Markets|date=3 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.cnbc.com/gallery/?video=3000474085&play=1|title=The Value of Social Impact Investing|publisher=CNBC|date=5 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Money/zUAtjqMbZOFHGVgKF0qyTJ/Jim-Roth--We-will-invest-515-million-across-portfolio-com.html|title=Jim Roth We Will Invest $5-15 Million Across Portfolio Companies|publisher=Livemint|author=Shrija Agrawal|date=20 April 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://video.cnbc.com/gallery/?video=3000274004|title=Microinsurance: What's It All About?|publisher=CNBC|date=8 May 2014}}</ref>
